text: Midland High School is a three-story public high school located in Midland, Michigan. It is the older of two high schools in the Midland Public Schools district, and a member of the Saginaw Valley High School Association. == Demographics == The demographic breakdown of the 1,392 students enrolled in 2015-16 was: * Male - 48.7% * Female - 51.3% * American Indian/Alaska Native - .4% * Asian- 1.4% * Black - 2.8% * Hispanic - 2.7% * Native Hawaiian/Pacific Islander - .1% * White - 91.5% * Multiracial - 1.2% 27.3% of the students were eligible for free or reduced-cost lunch. ==IB Diploma== Midland participate in the International Baccalaureate Diploma Programme. ==Notable alumni== *Howard Mudd, (born 1942) 3-time Pro Bowl offensive guard for the San Francisco 49ers; currently Indianapolis Colts assistant coach *Cathy Guisewite, (born 1950) cartoonist who created the comic strip Cathy in 1976 *Terry Collins, MLB manager (New York Mets, Anaheim Angels, Houston Astros) *Larry Jaster, former MLB player (St. Louis Cardinals, Montreal Expos, Atlanta Braves) *Jim Kern, former MLB pitcher (Cleveland Indians, Milwaukee Brewers) *Paul Emmel, MLB umpire *Kevin Mahar, former MLB player (minor league of the Texas Rangers) *Roger L. Worsley (Class of 1955), higher education administrator *Andrew Maxwell, football player for Michigan State University * Andrew Wylie (Class of 2012), Offensive tackle for the Kansas City Chiefs ==References== ==External links== * Category:Public high schools in Michigan Category:Midland, Michigan Category:Educational institutions established in 1872 Category:Schools in Midland County, Michigan Category:1872 establishments in Michigan
